text:
Well known for claypot dishes.

Totally not recommended for lunch time as stall allows for 'regular daily' customers to call in and order, then 'walk-in' customers will have to wait as long as an hour just to order.

When highlighted to him that this is not a fair queuing system, stall simply replied that he got no choice as these are regular customers.

Well... then perhaps should patronise this stall only if you are a regular.
Best claypot in Tuas area, too bad the place close now.
